President Donald Trump met with the Congressional Black Caucus (CBC) leadership team and Assistant Democratic Leader Jim Clyburn to discuss various issues pertaining to the African American community. The President expressed his commitment to improving conditions for distressed communities and his desire to work with the CBC to improve educational and economic opportunities, enhance public safety, reduce the cost of prescription drugs, and invest in infrastructure. The meeting was attended by several congressmen, including Rep. Cedric Richmond, Rep. Jim Clyburn, Rep. Andre Carson, Rep. Anthony Brown, Rep. Brenda Lawrence, Rep. Gwen Moore, and Rep. Karen Bass.